column2: The Baptist church is the Christian branch of the South. It sprode along the Cedar Key-Coast  during the early 21st-century, and is really popular amongst the people around the Mississippi as well.

Inuit paganism is mix of Shamanism and Animism. Like other Pagan religions, it varies wastly from tribe to tribe. There's many animist pantheons and gods, all of which have their own duties and regions in the religion. Religious rituals are led by the Angakkuq, a Shaman like priest in the religion.

Methodism started of as an sect in the Anglica church, but later on it became a Baptist heresy. It was found by an English cleric John Wesley.
The Native American religion is shattered and diverse. Every tribes history is written on their own totem pole represented by different types of animals and creatures.
Reformed Totemism has a organized set of beliefs and a holy book of their own.
Native American tribes write down their history on their totem poles represented by their various animal deities.

Voodoo or Vodoun is a Syncretic religion that originated from the west-African slaves. It's unorganized and like most of the other pagan religions has many gods and deities. This religion sprode across the Colobia and is the dominant religion there. A lots of pirate beliefs and traditions have been intergrated to the religion.

Calvinism is a branch of Protestantism found and named by a French theologian Jean Calvin in the 16th century. It represents the whole Reformed church in game, and covers Holland, Scotland and Switzerland.

Lutheranis was found by Martin Luther, a man who opposed the corruption of the Catholic church in early 15th century. His original goal was to not divide, but reform the church to the older and more traditional ways. This, however, failed and gave birth to various Protestant churches.
Anglicanism is the religion of England and Wales. It is a reformed religion like Calvinism and Lutheranism, founded as a protest against the Catholic church.

The Statue of Liberty used to be the symbol of the American dream. This huge bronze statue was destroyed during the events of the second civil war, and is now just a monument and attracts some tourists here and there. Maybe it will be rebuilt from the ashes one day...
The Statue of Liberty is the symbol of freedom, succes and American dream. It has been finally rebuilt and attracts millions of tourists each year.

The Statue of Liberty has been rebuilt from the ashes of the War. This monument has been a symbol for freedom, justice and succes since the old days and even after the War. Many tourists have decided to pay visit in this rebuilt wonder, which has been said to be originally built in a land historians call 'France'. This day, sure is a beginning of a new era!
